Former ANC
MP Vytjie Mentor is testifying at the commission of inquiry into state capture. In 2016
Mentor claimed on Facebook that the Gupta family had offered her a post as
public enterprises minister, just before Barbara Hogan was ousted. Mentor said that former president Jacob Zuma was in the
house in another room when the Guptas offered her job of minister of Public
Enterprises in exchange she had to drop the lucrative SAA route to India in
favour of their company. 